{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"972ec82a-10d7-4dea-a74c-3e2fa80b7bd8","content":"Yes, you will hit **target framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 dropped support for EOL runtimes. Here's the breakdown for your three targets:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped |\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for .NET (Core) targets. Two of your three TFMs (`netcoreapp3.1`, `net5.0`) are end-of-life and unsupported.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to something like:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\nBeyond TFMs, MSTest v3 also has some API-level changes (e.g., around `Assert` methods, attributes). Would you like me to perform the full migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d316b3c4-6729-4cca-a924-cc8a2a46406a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1` with MSTest v2.2.10. Let me check the MSTest v3 compatibility requirements.\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for several older target frameworks. Specifically:\n- MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET 6.0 for .NET Core/.NET targets, and .NET Framework 4.6.2 is still supported.\n- Actually, let me think more carefully. MSTest v3 supports:\n  - .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n  - .NET 6.0+\n  - .NET Core 3.1 was dropped in MSTest v3\n\nSo MSTest v3 only supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and .NET 6.0 and above, which means the user's `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` targets won't be compatible with the upgrade.","outputTokens":663,"requestId":"0429:329604:16A2CA1:181536C:6A033806"},"id":"0a26f66e-5bca-474c-ad3d-a347edb2d0ba","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:24:24.499Z","parentId":"8829cd1c-d3b8-4820-b496-dae6e2fda42c"}
